==English==
===Phrase===
'''[[right]] [[back]]'''

# Used in several informal constructions to indicate [[return]] -- especially [[imminent]] return to a point of origin. 
#: ''I'll be '''right back''''' --- means "I will return very soon." 
#: ''We're '''right back''' where we started'' --- means that an endeavor has progressed in a manner such that no real progress has yet been made.
#: '''''Right back''' at you'' --- expresses the same sentiment toward a person who has just paid a compliment (or given an insult) to the speaker.

===Noun===
'''right back'''
#(''association football'') a [[defender]] who normally plays on the right side of the field

